addition.26: * Implementation detail for the internal structure of {@link Range} instances. Represents a unique
addition.27: * way of "cutting" a "number line" (actually of instances of type {@code C}, not necessarily
addition.28: * "numbers") into two sections; this can be done below a certain value, above a certain value,
addition.29: * below all values or above all values. With this object defined in this way, an interval can
addition.30: * always be represented by a pair of {@code Cut} instances.
